   191  					Expect(req.Header["X-Request-Id"]).ToNot(BeNil())
   192  					Expect(req.Header["X-Request-Id"][0]).To(Equal(fmt.Sprintf("%v", "testString")))

   197  			})

   200  					URL:           testServer.URL,
   201  					Authenticator: &core.NoAuthAuthenticator{},
   202  				})

   216

  4743  					defer GinkgoRecover()
  4744

  4748

  4750  					Expect(req.Header.Get("Content-Encoding")).To(BeEmpty())
  4751  
  4752  					// If there is a body, then make sure we can read it
  4753  					bodyBuf := new(bytes.Buffer)
  4754  					if req.Header.Get("Content-Encoding") == "gzip" {
  4755  						body, err := core.NewGzipDecompressionReader(req.Body)
  4756  						Expect(err).To(BeNil())
  4757  						_, err = bodyBuf.ReadFrom(body)
  4758  						Expect(err).To(BeNil())
  4759  					} else {
  4760  						_, err := bodyBuf.ReadFrom(req.Body)
  4761  						Expect(err).To(BeNil())
  4762  					}
  4763  					fmt.Fprintf(GinkgoWriter, "  Request body: %s", bodyBuf.String())
  4764  
  4765  					Expect(req.Header["X-Correlation-Id"]).ToNot(BeNil())
  4766  					Expect(req.Header["X-Correlation-Id"][0]).To(Equal(fmt.Sprintf("%v", "testString")))
  4767  					Expect(req.Header["X-Request-Id"]).ToNot(BeNil())

  4769  					// Sleep a short time to support a timeout test

  4771  
  4772  					// Set mock response

  7809  					defer GinkgoRecover()

  7817

  7819  					bodyBuf := new(bytes.Buffer)
  7820  					if req.Header.Get("Content-Encoding") == "gzip" {
  7821  						body, err := core.NewGzipDecompressionReader(req.Body)
  7822  						Expect(err).To(BeNil())
  7823  						_, err = bodyBuf.ReadFrom(body)
  7824  						Expect(err).To(BeNil())
  7825  					} else {
  7826  						_, err := bodyBuf.ReadFrom(req.Body)

 14656  func CreateMockByteArray(mockData string) *[]byte {
 14657  	ba := make([]byte, 0)
 14658  	ba = append(ba, mockData...)
 14659  	return &ba
 14660  }
 14661  
 14662  func CreateMockUUID(mockData string) *strfmt.UUID {
 14663  	uuid := strfmt.UUID(mockData)
 14664  	return &uuid
 14665  }
 14666  
 14667  func CreateMockReader(mockData string) io.ReadCloser {
 14668  	return io.NopCloser(bytes.NewReader([]byte(mockData)))
 14669  }

 14671  func CreateMockDate(mockData string) *strfmt.Date {
 14672  	d, err := core.ParseDate(mockData)

 14674  		return nil
 14675  	}
 14676  	return &d
 14677  }
